text:
Looks like you're so enthusiast reading that.
Is that a recipe book?

Yeah. We were talking about making
lunch together sometime.

I'm discovering a lot of new things from this.
Um Producer, what do you prefer for lunch?

Karaage from bento boxes tastes different
from freshly fried ones, doesn't it?

Fufu, I get it. I'll try making it because
it's still juicy even when it's cold.

Tamagoyaki are so unique in each family.
I always use the dashi stock to make it.

Howa, in our place we like it sweet...
Fufu, maybe we can all bring our own.

It's like a taste of home...
It's a nice side dish to have, isn't it.

It's good to make ahead of time,
and it's in my repertoire.
